data.template:
DEEP RESEARCH BRIEF
===================
Topic: {{ topic }}
Target subreddits: {{ upstream['reddit']['subreddits'] }}
Platforms: {{ platforms | default('instagram,tiktok,linkedin,twitter') }}

-- OUTPUT PRIORITY (for every downstream agent) --
1. Surfacing recent, concrete happenings beats generic advice: new product launches, funding rounds, model/tool releases, research papers getting buzz, acquisitions, regulator moves — but ONLY when they appear below in Reddit/Serper/Instagram data.
2. Name-check specific companies/products/papers/events when they are in the signals; invent nothing.
3. Turn those facts into emotionally sharp hooks (why this matters NOW for audience) tied to '{{ topic }}'. Prefer Instagram captions/hashtags when the Instagram section lists real posts.
If the signals lack fresh news, say so briefly and pivot to evergreen pain + curiosity hooks grounded in threads/search/hashtag results.

--- REDDIT COMMUNITY SIGNALS ---
{{ upstream['reddit']['text'] }}

--- WEB TREND RESEARCH ---
{{ upstream['serper']['text'] }}

--- INSTAGRAM HASHTAG SIGNALS (Apify) ---
{{ upstream['instagram']['text'] }}

data.task_description_template:
Topic: {{ topic }}

Research signals:
{{ upstream['merge_signals']['text'] }}

Produce a memo that merges psychology WITH timeliness:
- List 5-10 recent-happening snippets lifted from signals (bullet: event + Why people care).
If signals have no usable recent specifics, explicitly write "Limited recent specificity in feeds" and derive evergreen hooks.

Topic: {{ topic }}

Audience psychology + timeliness memo:
{{ upstream['psych']['text'] }}

Design 6 viral content angles. For each angle specify which specific signal-backed fact/tool/brand/debate/person it leans on. If insufficient fresh facts existed in your upstream memo, mark that angle clearly as evergreen-fallback rooted in Reddit language.

Topic: {{ topic }}

Angles (already tied to timeliness cues):
{{ upstream['angles']['text'] }}

For each angle, write 2 variations. Hooks must EITHER open with a concrete named recent detail from the memo OR deliberately say you're zooming evergreen if no fact fit — never invent news. Include a subtle why-now framing when events exist.

Topic: {{ topic }}

Copy pack:
{{ upstream['copy']['text'] }}

Brief each variation including how to visually cue recency/news (carousel slide with headline summary, screenshot-style frame, caption timestamp language, comparison table of tools, etc.).

Topic: {{ topic }}

Annotated content pack:
{{ upstream['creative_brief']['text'] }}

Rank all variations — explicitly note timeliness/specific-signal leverage in each rationale (+5 to +15 mental bonus if hook clearly rides a documented event). Penalise vague sensationalism unrelated to briefing.
